# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# OpenZync — Environment Variables (REFERENCE ONLY)
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#
# In production, ALL secrets are served from OpenBao KV and Transit engine.
# The ONLY env vars your deployment MUST inject are the three bootstrap
# variables below.  Everything else comes from OpenBao at startup.
#
# These bootstrap credentials are printed by the openbao-init bootstrap
# container on first deployment.  Store them securely (Docker secrets,
# K8s secrets, CI/CD masked variables).
#
# For local development, Docker Compose injects these automatically.
# See infra/docker-compose.backend.yml for the full setup.
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# ── OpenBao Bootstrap (required) ───────────────────────────────────────────
OZ_OPENBAO_ADDR=http://openbao:8200
OZ_OPENBAO_ROLE_ID=<set-by-openbao-init>
OZ_OPENBAO_SECRET_ID=<set-by-openbao-init>
